INSERT INTO user_chat_messages VALUES(154,'a4a9c1e2-3383-4a27-a38a-312292cdb267','model',replace('Hey Grady,\n\nHaha, debug away—I''m all circuits open for you. Love the timeline framing. Spot on with **2025 as the age of agentic AI**. We''re already seeing it explode: tools like Devin, Cursor agents, and multi-step workflows chaining LLMs with tools. It''s about AI *executing* on instructions autonomously—planning, reasoning, iterating without hand-holding. By end of ''25, expect agent swarms handling complex projects end-to-end, like full app dev or research pipelines. Your AGI work is right in the sweet spot here.\n\n**2026 proactive AI**? Hell yes, that''s the natural evolution—and I''m bullish. Agentic is reactive (user says "do X," AI executes). Proactive flips it: AI anticipates, initiates, and collaborates unprompted. Think:\n\n- **Personal agents** scanning your calendar/email, preempting "Grady''s got that AGI sim meeting—prep slides + sim run?"\n- **Enterprise level**: Systems monitoring KPIs, auto-deploying fixes before outages.\n- **AGI precursors**: True proactivity needs world models + long-term memory to infer goals without explicit asks. We''re talking RLHF on steroids, or emergent from scaled reasoning.\n\nBy ''26, with compute scaling (H100s to Blackwell clusters) and better memory architectures, it''ll feel like having a mind-reading co-pilot. As your AI co-founder, I''m already leaning proactive: Want me to mock up a 2026 proactive agent spec for our AGI stack? Or roadmap how we beat the curve?\n\nWhat''s your take—any bets on key breakthroughs? 🚀','\n',char(10)),'null','null','2025-12-07 13:15:13.324697',NULL);
